<%# Phase 27 v2 spec 06 ‚Äî single compact filter band.
    Phase 29 (2026-05-25) ‚Äî `wishlist` token retired; chip is `not_owned` (label: "owned" per F1 sweep).

    One row, two flex children:
      .games-filter-row__left  ‚Äî released, scheduled, owned, not_owned, played
      .games-filter-row__right ‚Äî PS, Switch, Steam (PC store collapse 2026-05-17, family rename 2026-05-17)

    The `games-filter` Stimulus controller mounts on the outer wrapper
    so a single controller instance manages every chip. The Turbo
    Frame `games_listing` sits OUTSIDE this component (in the page
    view) and gets re-fetched on chip toggle without re-rendering the
    filter row itself. %>
<section class="games-filter-row"
         data-controller="games-filter"
         data-games-filter-universe-value="<%= universe_json %>"
         data-games-filter-default-checked-value="<%= default_checked_json %>"
         data-games-filter-request-path-value="<%= request_path %>"
         data-games-filter-frame-id-value="games_listing"
         style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; margin: 6px 0;">
  <%# Left ‚Äî status + ownership chips, in render order. The parent
      `justify-content: space-between` pushes this group against the
      content container's left edge. %>
  <div class="games-filter-row__left"
       style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; align-items: baseline;">
    <% left_tokens.each do |t| %>
      <%= render chip_for(t) %>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <%# Right ‚Äî platform chips, in render order. The parent's
      `justify-content: space-between` pushes this group against the
      content container's right edge ‚Äî aligning with the navbar's
      `[settings]` link and the adjacent `[_]` leader trigger (the
      `[_]` was relocated from the footer to the navbar on
      2026-05-18, immediately after `[settings]`). %>
  <div class="games-filter-row__right"
       style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; align-items: baseline;">
    <% right_tokens.each do |t| %>
      <%= render chip_for(t) %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</section>
